26:50.599 --> 26:51.899
Ella. Look at that

26:53.799 --> 26:56.099
May be we go there with Tim?

26:56.799 --> 27:00.749
- I've my work to do. You take him
- I'll stay aboard if you want to go

27:01.949 --> 27:04.099
I have no time. You go

27:05.399 --> 27:08.949
Come along, Joe?
Stretch for your legs

27:09.899 --> 27:11.399
Yes, all right

27:22.399 --> 27:24.399
Here we are

27:25.399 --> 27:27.249
Watch me

27:30.599 --> 27:34.099
- Yes, yes, that one!
- Got it

27:34.134 --> 27:35.499
2 pence.

27:35.749 --> 27:37.499
You see, I always win

27:38.099 --> 27:40.049
How do you like it, son?

27:41.899 --> 27:44.949
- And that's it
- You are touching the line, sorry

27:45.049 --> 27:48.499
- Excuse me, I was not touching the line
- You touched the line

27:52.399 --> 27:54.914
What are you doing here?

27:54.949 --> 27:58.149
- I'm working here now
- Right, right, Bob. This is Joe Huggy.

27:58.184 --> 27:59.766
He works with us
couple of months

27:59.801 --> 28:01.314
- Nice to meet you, Joe.
- Me too

28:01.349 --> 28:04.799
Me and Les, we used to
work on the same boat

28:04.849 --> 28:07.049
- Never the same shipyard
- No

28:07.299 --> 28:09.849
- That was good time?
- Yes

28:10.199 --> 28:11.949
2 pence.

28:12.449 --> 28:14.414
Bob, here is my son, Jim.

28:14.449 --> 28:17.349
- Jim, this is Bob.
- We close the game

28:17.449 --> 28:20.464
<i>I don't want to go
back to the barge</i>

28:20.499 --> 28:23.699
Do you want to go to the picture?
There are two of them in town

28:23.734 --> 28:25.516
- Do you want to go to the picture?
- Yae

28:25.551 --> 28:27.264
Joe, do you want to
go to the picture?

28:27.299 --> 28:30.799
No, no. I'll walk into town
then go back to the barge

28:31.299 --> 28:33.249
Let make it quick

28:55.449 --> 28:58.399
Go, Joe. I don't
want to see you

28:59.299 --> 29:00.749
Go

29:17.699 --> 29:20.649
Look what you've done

29:24.149 --> 29:25.849
Give it to me

29:38.349 --> 29:40.249
