30:53.299 --> 30:54.849
Hello, Joe.

30:55.049 --> 30:56.299
Hello, Cathie.

30:59.199 --> 31:00.849
What are you doing here?

31:03.349 --> 31:06.899
- I'm working here by the river
- You are working?

31:07.299 --> 31:10.449
Joe Taylor condescend to
mix with the working class?

31:10.899 --> 31:12.899
I don't take any pride in it

31:15.749 --> 31:18.649
I see you never
made it to China

31:22.549 --> 31:25.599
- Your flat is still there?
- Yes

31:26.249 --> 31:28.549
I've got a flat mate now

31:29.399 --> 31:31.299
Is she nice?

31:31.449 --> 31:33.199
I don't see her much

31:35.949 --> 31:38.299
Why barge, Joe?

31:38.849 --> 31:41.599
You can find work
more glamorous

31:43.099 --> 31:45.399
Just sort of have it, really

31:46.899 --> 31:50.549
- What about you, you still at the office?
- Yes

31:52.849 --> 31:55.149
Nothing's really changed

31:56.399 --> 31:58.299
Except us

32:06.249 --> 32:09.649
- What did you do with all my stuff?
- I threw them away

32:10.899 --> 32:13.099
As you told me to

32:14.999 --> 32:17.099
I thought I would
never see you again

35:39.999 --> 35:43.599
- Hi gentlemen
- Go, Joe.

35:44.949 --> 35:47.599
- You sure?
- I'm scaling a little

35:47.634 --> 35:49.949
It'll get hot in an hour

37:05.099 --> 37:07.199
Joe, get some sacs of coal

37:15.249 --> 37:19.149
- Tim!
- Easy said than done

37:19.699 --> 37:21.499
We continue?

37:22.099 --> 37:24.099
Put it in the back
of the truck, Joe.

37:24.749 --> 37:27.099
- It's in your truck now
- Thanks

37:27.499 --> 37:29.449
What about the boy

37:30.049 --> 37:33.949
- Will you come to see him?
- He'll be back in school again next week

37:35.699 --> 37:38.399
I have some surprise for you

37:40.249 --> 37:41.449
A banana!

37:41.649 --> 37:44.249
- What should you say?
- Thank you, uncle Sam.

37:46.799 --> 37:49.349
- Thanks
- Will you talk about the naked lady?

37:49.599 --> 37:53.099
- Yes, some pervert has done it
- Me and Joe found her

37:53.134 --> 37:55.549
- You're joking
- We called the police

37:55.599 --> 37:57.549
Will you stop
talking about this?

37:57.799 --> 37:59.799
All talk about it

38:38.749 --> 38:41.099
Drink your tea

39:08.749 --> 39:10.199
Say bye to your dad

39:10.349 --> 39:12.999
- Bye, dad
- Bye, son. Take care of yourself

39:18.449 --> 39:20.449
- Take care
- Bye

40:00.349 --> 40:02.849
You're sad about Tim?

40:04.499 --> 40:07.399
He needs an education.

40:08.649 --> 40:12.499
But when he goes
away It breaks my heart

42:14.249 --> 42:18.149
<i>Think of me when you look at
yourself. With undying love, C.</i>

42:23.599 --> 42:26.099
I had a dream
about you yesterday

42:27.249 --> 42:29.799
I don't think for months

42:31.999 --> 42:35.099
- I think you have gone away
- I had gone away

42:35.899 --> 42:38.699
I shed my own skin
and hide in the fog

42:41.199 --> 42:43.149
I am pregnant

42:44.149 --> 42:45.499
It's yours

42:47.849 --> 42:49.299
Two months has gone

42:52.549 --> 42:56.999
- Two months and you wanted me out of your life?
- This isn't going to happen

42:57.999 --> 43:00.449
Is there anything you
want me to do about it?

43:02.099 --> 43:04.649
I just thought
you should know who

43:07.749 --> 43:11.199
You could marry me and we'll
make wonderful babies together

43:13.199 --> 43:15.049
Kid is not exactly I see it

43:15.599 --> 43:18.064
Why not, Joe? What
are you afraid of?

43:18.099 --> 43:22.099
There's a kid in the barge and I spent every
moment I want to kick him out of the sight

43:22.799 --> 43:25.049
You don't have to be like that
We'll work out intelligently

43:25.149 --> 43:26.814
It's not about us

43:26.849 --> 43:29.599
It's about what
kids do to people

43:30.649 --> 43:34.149
Cathie, I am not someone you
want to marry and you know that

43:44.049 --> 43:46.749
- Have you been seeing anyone else?
- It's your child, Joe.

43:46.784 --> 43:48.949
That doesn't
answer my question

43:53.149 --> 43:55.299
His name is Dan,
he's a plumber

43:57.049 --> 43:59.849
He's nice but I'm not
really interested in him

43:59.899 --> 44:02.499
- He's married anyway
- That's why you said it's mine

44:02.549 --> 44:04.499
It's the truth

44:05.649 --> 44:07.449
I have to get
back to the barge

44:07.599 --> 44:10.099
Don't run away, we can
sort it out together

44:10.149 --> 44:12.324
No, we can't. I'm
not yours anymore

44:12.359 --> 44:14.499
That's not true

44:14.949 --> 44:17.124
We were right,
we were fearless

44:17.351 --> 44:18.351
I was... then.
I have to go

44:20.749 --> 44:22.714
But Joe, what about the baby?

44:22.749 --> 44:24.814
I'll send some money
when I have some

44:24.849 --> 44:26.749
I looked after you
for more than two years

44:26.799 --> 44:28.799
You owe me more...

44:28.834 --> 44:30.799
Bye, Cathie.

47:13.199 --> 47:16.299
- Joe, do you want to get on? - No,
I'll see you at the next lock. - All right.

47:43.299 --> 47:44.999
Look at that, Joe

47:46.099 --> 47:49.499
Daniel Gordon, plumber
of 26 years old in Glasgow

47:49.549 --> 47:52.899
was in custody charged with
murder of Catherine Dimly,

47:52.934 --> 47:54.249
A future actress

47:54.299 --> 47:56.749
Dimly's body was
discovered 2 weeks ago

47:56.799 --> 47:59.849
by two bargemen where they
recovered it from the River Clay

48:00.499 --> 48:02.699
They'll hang that men for sure

48:04.149 --> 48:06.599
Well, we're going to celebrate

48:06.649 --> 48:09.949
Not every day I'm
mentioned in the papers

48:25.449 --> 48:26.999
Here, Joe.

49:07.549 --> 49:10.849
- Joe, I'm going for a beer. Do you want to come?
- No, I'll finish this

49:11.599 --> 49:12.699
Serve yourself

49:12.949 --> 49:15.449
